%U A395816 1057198980466907795111869,1574659518193293073896953,1651613100316182634822211,2579882148294177281806591,2681186855821233923845067,3045998278981289844695333
%N A395816 Brier numbers that have at least two covering sets.
%H A395816 Emilia Gurisatti, <a href="/A395816/b395816.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..29</a>
%H A395816 Emilia Gurisatti, <a href="https://github.com/emiguri/brierdouble/blob/main/brierdouble.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..29 with its covering sets</a>
%H A395816 Wilfrid Keller, <a href="http://www.prothsearch.com/briernums.html">A Collection of Brier Numbers</a>
%H A395816 Carlos Rivera, <a href="https://www.primepuzzles.net/problems/prob_092.htm">Problem 92. Multiple covering sets for Sierpinski and for Riesel integers</a>, The Prime Puzzles & Problems Connection.
%e A395816 For every k >= 1, 216644304573327922644547*2^k + 1 has a divisor in the set {3, 5, 7, 11, 17, 19, 31, 37, 41, 61, 73, 97, 109, 151, 241, 257, 331, 673} and also in the set {3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 31, 37, 61, 73, 97, 109, 151, 241, 257, 331, 673}. For every k >= 1, 216644304573327922644547*2^k - 1 has a divisor in the set {3, 5, 7, 11, 17, 19, 31, 37, 41, 61, 73, 97, 109, 151, 241, 257, 331, 673} and also in the set {3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 31, 37, 61, 73, 97, 109, 151, 241, 257, 331, 673}. 216644304573327922644547 is therefore in the sequence.
%Y A395816 Cf. A076335, A076336, A076337, A263391, A263392.
